16/05/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and his Pakistani counterpart, Shaukat Aziz, met in Athens on Monday (15 May) and announced that their countries are willing to boost bilateral political and economic co-operation.
A bilateral agreement on collaboration in tourism was sealed within the framework of the visit.
Karamanlis said they also discussed issues related to Iraq, Afghanistan, the Middle East and combating terrorism, as well as boosting regional co-operation and stability in the Balkans.
(Kathimerini - 16/05/06;
ANA, ERT - 15/05/06)
